This page provides a list of the FHIR artifacts defined as part of this implementation guide.


Structures: Resource Profiles {% capture grouping_desc %}These define constraints on FHIR resources for systems conforming to this implementation guide.{% endcapture %}
    {{ grouping_desc | markdownify}}





               ACVPU Consciousness Level

            {% capture desc %}ACVPU consciousness level assessment for NEWS2 (Alert, Confusion, Voice, Pain, Unresponsive){% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Barthel Index

            {% capture desc %}Barthel Index for measuring independence in activities of daily living (ADL). Score 0-20=total dependency, 91-99=slight dependency, 100=independent. Total range 0-100.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Blood Pressure

            {% capture desc %}Blood pressure observation for NEWS2 (systolic BP used for scoring){% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Body Temperature

            {% capture desc %}Body temperature observation for NEWS2{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Braden Scale Assessment

            {% capture desc %}A profile for the Braden Scale pressure ulcer risk assessment{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Glasgow Coma Scale

            {% capture desc %}Glasgow Coma Scale (GCS) for assessing level of consciousness. Total score 3-15 with three required components: Eye (1-4), Verbal (1-5), Motor (1-6).{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Goal Evaluation

            {% capture desc %}Evaluation of patient goal outcomes and nursing intervention effectiveness. Assesses whether goals have been met, partially met, or not met. Part of the ADPIE framework's Evaluation phase.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Heart Rate

            {% capture desc %}Heart rate (pulse) observation for NEWS2{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Inspired Oxygen

            {% capture desc %}Inspired oxygen observation for NEWS2 (air vs supplemental oxygen){% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               MUST Score (Malnutrition Universal Screening Tool)

            {% capture desc %}Malnutrition Universal Screening Tool for identifying adults at risk of malnutrition. Score 0=low risk, 1=medium risk, 2+=high risk. NHS-standard nutritional screening.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Mini Mental State Examination (MMSE)

            {% capture desc %}Mini Mental State Examination for cognitive function screening. Score 24-30=no impairment, 18-23=mild, 0-17=severe. Total range 0-30.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Monk Skin Tone Observation

            {% capture desc %}Observation of patient skin tone using the Monk Skin Tone Scale (10-point scale A-J). Provides more granular skin tone assessment than Fitzpatrick scale, particularly for darker skin tones. Supports equitable care and accurate clinical assessment across diverse populations.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Morse Fall Scale

            {% capture desc %}Morse Fall Scale for assessing fall risk. Score 0-24=no risk, 25-50=low risk, ≥51=high risk. Total range 0-125.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               NEWS2 Score

            {% capture desc %}National Early Warning Score 2 (NEWS2) for detecting clinical deterioration. Fully aligned with NHS CareConnect-NEWS2-Observation-1.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               NEWS2 Sub-Score

            {% capture desc %}Individual parameter sub-score for NEWS2 (0-3 for most parameters). References the related vital sign observation.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Nursing Intervention

            {% capture desc %}Nursing intervention or procedure performed to achieve patient goals. Documents actions taken by nursing staff to address identified problems and achieve desired outcomes. Part of the ADPIE framework's Implementation phase.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Nursing Problem

            {% capture desc %}Nursing diagnosis or problem identified during assessment. Represents clinical judgments about individual, family, or community responses to actual or potential health problems. Part of the ADPIE framework's Diagnosis phase.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               ONC NHS Patient

            {% capture desc %}A patient profile for use in NHS nursing contexts with ethnic category extension.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Open Nursing Core Assessment

            {% capture desc %}Base profile for nursing assessment observations conforming to UK Core standards. Captures structured nursing assessment data as part of the ADPIE (Assessment, Diagnosis, Planning, Implementation, Evaluation) nursing process framework. Used as parent for specialized assessments like NEWS2, Braden Scale, and clinical observations.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Oxygen Saturation

            {% capture desc %}Oxygen saturation (SpO2) observation for NEWS2{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Pain Assessment (NRS 0-10)

            {% capture desc %}Pain severity assessment using the Numeric Rating Scale (0-10){% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Patient Goal

            {% capture desc %}Patient-centered goal established in response to identified nursing problems. Defines measurable outcomes and addresses specific nursing diagnoses. Part of the ADPIE framework's Planning phase.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Respiration Rate

            {% capture desc %}Respiration rate observation for NEWS2{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Skin Tone Observation

            {% capture desc %}Observation of patient skin tone using the Fitzpatrick skin type classification. Supports equitable care by enabling skin tone-aware clinical decision making, particularly for conditions that present differently across skin tones (e.g., pressure ulcers, cyanosis).{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Waterlow Score

            {% capture desc %}Waterlow Pressure Ulcer Risk Assessment - NHS standard tool. Score ≥10 indicates at risk, ≥15 high risk, ≥20 very high risk.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Wound Assessment

            {% capture desc %}Comprehensive wound assessment including staging and dimensions{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               qSOFA (Quick SOFA)

            {% capture desc %}Quick Sequential Organ Failure Assessment for sepsis screening. Score ≥2 indicates high risk. Total range 0-3.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}





Structures: Extension Definitions {% capture grouping_desc %}These define constraints on FHIR data types for systems conforming to this implementation guide.{% endcapture %}
    {{ grouping_desc | markdownify}}





               Intervention Goal Reference

            {% capture desc %}Extension to link nursing interventions to the patient goals they are intended to achieve. Supports goal-directed care planning and intervention tracking.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Observation Goal Reference

            {% capture desc %}Extension to link goal evaluation observations to the patient goals being evaluated. Enables tracking of goal progress and outcomes over time.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               UK Core Ethnic Category

            {% capture desc %}An extension to record the ethnic category of a patient, as per UK Core standards.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}





